{
  "texts": [
    "For the HCRs, Martinez and Sá (2020) did not only search for all papers published by the HCRs, but also academic CVs using a database provided by the Brazilian National Council for Scientific and Technological Development (Brasília).",
    "The empirical results of the study have been summarized by the authors as follows: \"connections with core countries in the global North are critical for most of Brazil's highly cited researchers.",
    "Most of these scientists work at prestigious public universities and are inserted in international research networks.",
    "While all but one of them obtained their PhDs from Brazilian universities, they have been internationally mobile from the early stages of their careers\" (p. 51).",
    "For investigating Chinese research success, Li (2018) analyzed HCRs lists from 2001, 2014, 2015, and 2016 and additionally government funding data from the Chinese National Science Foundation (Peking)."
  ]
}